CH. 1. delectus] It was not a matter of course that he should succeed his fatherin the command : there were several able officers there, as Cerialis, Placidus, and the elder Trajan. And the anarchy of the last year had so demoralised public feeling, that Titus after his victory, as well as Domitian now (iv. 86. 2), were suspected of disaffection to their father.

privatis . . . ciarus] See on ii. 77. 2. Titus had also distinguished himself in the earlier part of the Jewish war, before the death of Nero. Privatis is a sels-evident correction for filulis, zie. praelatis.
